
[1]ergot

   ERGOT, n. In farriery, a stub, like a piece of soft horn, about the
   bigness of a chestnut, situated behind and below the pastern joint, and
   commonly hid under the tuft of the fetloc.

   1. A morbid excrescence in grain; a dark colored shoot, often an inch
   long, from the ears of grain, particularly of rye.
